Identity of Target System.statement: Program Totality Analyzer (PTA) consists of a deterministic, evidence-citing analyzer CLI and libraries (Python) and a full-stack web app (Node.js/Express + React/Vite) for project management, analyses, and dossier/receipt review.

Architecture Snapshot.statement: PTA frontend is built with React 18 (TypeScript, Vite), Wouter for routing, shadcn/ui (Radix UI), and TailwindCSS, managing state/data with TanStack React Query.
The PTA backend is implemented with Node.js 20, Express 5, Drizzle ORM, esbuild, and includes session management with express-session and connect-pg-simple.
PTA requires PostgreSQL 14+ for persistent storage of projects, analyses, and conversations, with Drizzle migrations and env-driven database connectivity.
The Python-based analyzer is invoked as a child process by the Express API, provides deterministic structural analysis, and can produce outputs like operate.json and claims.json.

Backend/Dependencies.statement: Major backend dependencies include Express 5, Drizzle ORM, esbuild for building, connect-pg-simple for session store, pg for PostgreSQL connectivity, express-session for session management, and Zod for schema validation.

Frontend/Dependencies.statement: Frontend main dependencies are React 18, Vite, TailwindCSS, shadcn/ui (Radix UI), TanStack React Query, Wouter router, and Zod for shared types.

Python Analyzer/Dependencies.statement: The Python analyzer requires Python 3.11+, and depends on gitpython, jsonschema, openai, python-dotenv, rich, and typer.

Runtime Environment.statement: The main server runs as a Node.js process for both development and production; developed with live reload via tsx/Vite, built for production using npm run build.
The PTA system provides a Dockerfile for multi-stage build and exposes port 5000, but does not include Docker Compose, systemd, or reverse-proxy integration guides.

Configuration.statement: Critical configuration variables include DATABASE_URL, API_KEY, and SESSION_SECRET, to be set in the .env file.

Security.statement: Session cookies are encrypted/signed using the SESSION_SECRET as configured for express-session.
Secrets such as API keys and database credentials are never committed to the repository and are referenced only by name in .env files, using python-dotenv and Node env.
Database connections are presumed encrypted via Postgres driver, though no explicit TLS configuration evidence is found.

Data Storage.statement: PTA stores projects, analyses, session tokens, and chat logs (if applicable) in PostgreSQL, as defined in Drizzle schema.

API Surface.statement: The REST API is mounted under /api/, all requests/response bodies are JSON and Zod-validated, with documented endpoints such as /api/health, /api/ready, /api/projects, /api/audit/verify.

Build & Deployment.statement: Development server is started with npm run dev; production build is performed by npm run build, and production server starts with npm run start.

Capability Map.statement: PTA supports deterministic boot/install surveys, operator runbook synthesis, REST API surface extraction, explicit evidence/unknowns labeling, Replit-specific awareness, forensic export/verification, LLM-assisted findings, and audit chain verification.

Frontend/Build.statement: The frontend build is handled via Vite and TypeScript, configured to output to dist/public.

Frontend/Config.statement: TypeScript path aliases are set for shared types (as @shared/*) and assets/components/libraries for clean import structure.

Session/Auth.statement: No OAuth or password register/login flows are present—API access is enforced via API_KEY only.

Analyzer.statement: The analyzer can optionally use an LLM for interpretive analysis but defaults to deterministic (no LLM) operation.

Replit Execution Profile.statement: On Replit, PTA launches with npm run dev by default, exposes port 5000 mapped to 80, automatically detects Replit execution, and uses Vite plugins for dev error overlays.

Security/Posture.statement: Audit logging is implemented as a hash-linked, append-only chain, verifiable via API endpoints or forensic packs.

Install/Prereqs.statement: To run PTA, required tools are Node.js (20+), npm, TypeScript, Python 3.11+, PostgreSQL 14+, jq, unzip, and drizzle-kit.

Frontend/Styling.statement: Frontend uses TailwindCSS for styling, extended with custom color/tokens and animation configuration.

Type Safety.statement: API contracts and shared types are managed with TypeScript and Zod, and located in the shared directory.
